13/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan was unanimously re-elected leader of the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) at a congress on Sunday (12 October).
The only candidate nominated, he used the occasion to reassure Turkey's secularists.
"Our party has no secret agenda or aim.
We stand at an equal distance from all religious beliefs and cultures," he explained.
In remarks apparently directed at the Iraqi Ruling Council, Erdogan said Turkey's planned peacekeeping presence in Iraq "will definitely not include violence or occupation".
As for EU accession, he assured party members Turkey is closer than ever to membership.
(Hurriyet, Milliyet - 13/10/03;
AFP, NTV, TRT 2 - 12/10/03)
